INSERT INTO "blog_master" VALUES (1,'Where to List Your Rental Property for Maximum Exposure and Minimal Fees','Today’s rental market presents particular difficulties for both renters and property owners. Finding a property that meets their needs could be too much for tenants. Listing a rental property may be costly and laborious for homeowners. Fortunately, there are now websites that let you find rental listings by the owner and post your rental property for free, therefore simplifying and cheapening the procedure for everybody concerned.\r\n\r\nListing Your Rental Property for Free Is Rising\r\nListing a rental property no longer calls for paying large fees to a real estate agent. Many websites now let homeowners post their rental homes for free, so they directly interact with possible renters. This innovative approach lets landlords save money and yet reach a broad audience by removing the need for intermediaries. List your rental property for free gives you total control over the lease process, from pricing to inquiry handling.\r\n\r\nListing Your Rental Property for Free Is Rising\r\nListing a rental property no longer calls for paying large fees to a real estate agent. Many websites now let homeowners post their rental homes for free, so they directly interact with possible renters. This innovative approach lets landlords save money and yet reach a broad audience by removing the need for intermediaries. List your rental property for free gives you total control over the lease process, from pricing to inquiry handling.','2025-09-03 07:42:07',NULL),(3,'Eos consequatur es','<p>hello this the new content 2</p>','2025-09-03 10:11:15',NULL),(5,'Dummy Blog','<h2>Where Indoors and Outdoors Become One</h2><p><br></p><p>Step outside, and the magic deepens. The covered patio isn’t just an “extension” of the home—it <em>is</em> the home at its most alive. Imagine:</p><ol><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><strong>Sipping coffee at dawn</strong> on a plush lounge chair, the morning light spilling over the pool.</li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><strong>Hosting a summer dinner</strong> under the soft glow of recessed lighting, with the scent of grilled food and laughter filling the air.</li><li data-list=\"bullet\"><span class=\"ql-ui\" contenteditable=\"false\"></span><strong>Winding down at night</strong> with a book, the pool’s gentle ripples reflecting the stars.</li></ol><p><br></p><p>The patio’s open layout—complete with a built-in grill, dining table, and cozy seating—feels like a stage set for life’s best moments. And that’s the point: this space isn’t designed for show. It’s designed for <em>living</em>.</p>','2026-02-05 11:14:59',NULL),(6,'New Blog','<p>this is blog content</p>','2026-04-24 14:11:59',NULL);

